reviewText: I love this movie. My review is of the BLURAY poor quality not the movie itself.Stick with the DVD on the Practical Magic movie if you already own it. If not buy the streaming version instead! I will explain... This is not only a poor quality transfer to Bluray, it is a chopped up version of the full image of the movie!!!This is not true widescreen. They just slapped black bars on the top and bottom. I watched the Vudu Digital Streaming version and you can clearly see it is the original version without the black bars and chopped up images. This Bluray has actors heads cut off at the tops and images cut off at the bottom.(SEE THE PHOTOS I ADDED ON THE BLURAY LISTING FOR PRACTICAL MAGIC/WITCHES OF EASTWICK. PHOTOS TAKEN FROM MY TV OF BOTH VUDU STREAMING VERSION & BLURAY DVD VERSION. They are a little slanted from not having an exact camera angle but you can clearly see the Bluray DVD version is of inferior quality & image!!!)In scene 3, on the Bluray version you can see in the meal they are eating outside at the picnic table. (SEE PHOTOS showing this AT THE TOP OF THE BLURAY LISTING HERE) One of the aunts hat is cut off, and the other aunt you cannot see her dinner plate with the turkey leg. In the Vudu version you can clearly see the full hat and the dinner plate with the turkey leg. Also in the same scene both of the children's heads are cut off at the top.In the next scene with the two girls sitting in the stairwell the red head's legs are cut off as well as the top of her head.This goes on and on through the whole movie in the Bluray and DVD versions!!!!At first watching of the Bluray, I felt something was not right with the head cut off at the top. It was not until I saw the Vudu streaming version that I was able to put my finger on it and actually see full images of the movie.This is a terrible conversion with no picture quality enhancement from the DVD. It was not remastered whatsoever. May I also add the DVD has the same issues with the black bars slapped on the top and bottom. I own both bluray & dvd.******  If you have the DVD you can get a VUDU Digital streaming copy for only $2 in their Disc to Digital transfer program! It will give you the movie without the black bars and cut off image!!!!!Your first Disc to Digital is free too with Vudu!It also looks like the Amazon streaming version of this movie too!Don't waste your money on the Bluray or DVD of Practical Magic!
summary: Terrible BLURAY Transfer w Top &Bottom Pic Cut Off

reviewText: I enjoy Practical Magic, but abhorr Witches of Eastwick.  These two don't belong on the same disc.While both stories have their inaccuracies about witches, PM is enjoyable entertainment, while W of E is a big mistake.  I'm also not a fan of what's-his-name...Nickelson.PM has two great actresses in Weist and Channing, and youthful Bullock and Kidman, all are charming, as are their costars, well chosen for their parts. Delightful settings, wonderfully victorian style house by the sea, lovely coastal town with amusing residents, and of course - love stories too. A good time at the movies.W of E is about hapless would-be witches, dabbling with the devil, who by the way does not exist in witchcraft.  Nickelson is his usual sleezy self. Pointless movie.I suggest purchasing Practical Magic 'separately', gather your girlfriends, make some Marguaritas and settle in for a fun night's viewing.
summary: Enjoyed Practical Magic - Abhorred Witches of Eastwick.

reviewText: 7/1/10 RELEASE UPDATE:There really are no special features whatsover on this disc.  Warner Bros. has gotten super cheap.  Not even any French or Spanish language tracks, just subtitles and English captions (which are so annoying for those who aren't hearing impaired Warner Bros. should offer both captions and regular subtitles, as other studios do).Although picture and sound are great, there is some weird vibrating on Eastwick which is most apparent during the opening titles, like someone's slightly shaking the camera or something.ORIGINAL PREVIEW REVIEW:The Witches of Eastwick is one of the best movies ever made!  Despite its brilliance, Warner Bros. has never shown the movie the respect it deserves with a special edition DVD.  And now it's being slapped onto a double feature blu-ray disc with the bad, boring Practical Magic!  Ugh!  How insulting!Eastwick deserves a disc with docs, interviews, commentaries, etc.  Even the DVD has a music-only track as recognition of its brilliant score!  It's a far superior film - intelligent, unsentimental, deliciously clever, naughty with a brilliant script and some of the best monologues I've ever heard!  Not to mention one of the wittiest film adaptations I've ever seen!All I can remember thinking about Practical Magic the one time I saw it was, Is this thing ever going to END?!Warner Bros. should be ashamed, not only for dissing The Witches of Eastwick but for being so stupid!  Sure it's obvious to pair two witch movies (duh!) but Eastwick was box office smash whereas Practical Magic was DOA.I thought the greedy Hollywood studios were out to MAKE MONEY!!
summary: 7/1/10 Update - Bare Bones Disc (Eastwick Deserves More Respect!)

reviewText: I owned both movies on DVD. So the chance to upgrade in quality, plus cut down on shelf space was too good an opportunity to miss out on.The Witches of Eastwick is an excellent film and looks better than the DVD version (not really difficult to be honest). Given that this, and PM are both based in small towns, with plenty of greenery and water around, Blu-Ray should, in theory, really bring out the colours. I can't really complain too much about Witches, given that the film was made in 1987. Having said that, the Warner releases (double features) of the first 4 Dirty Harry films look AMAZING, and these were made before Witches.But i have a problem with Practical Magic. This film, if at all possible, looks WORSE on Blu-Ray than on regular DVD. What the hell have Warners done??!! At best, it's an exact copy over from DVD to HD. But it's evident that no cleaning up whatsoever was done.In my opinion, if studios are going to release older titles on HD format, then they should at least have the courtesy to put the effort in. Blu-Ray discs are certainly not cheap. And whilst i'm delighted to have a better copy of Eastwick, being saddled with a poor copy of PM doesn't make me an entirely satisfied customer.The 3 stars don't reflect the movies themselves, but if i could give individual stars for quality, it would be 3.5 for Eastwick and 0.5 for Magic.
summary: Practical Magic Blu-Ray not so magic

reviewText: EVERYONE SHOULD EXPERIENCE THE WITCHES OF EASTWICK.It's everything a movie should be. Actually much more, full of over-the-top actors, acting, Nicholson production, Sarandon, direction,Michel Feiffer, writing, and... h'm I'm having a devil of a time remembering other contributors... surprises, laughs, lessons. Over the years I've seen TWOE at least five times. Always something new to see and laugh, marvel at... but funny, I keep forgetting so much; I just know it was GREAT.PRACTICAL, MAGIC is less awing and more complex, with a plot that carries you through if you concentrate, but just a bit is okay. It's memorable, editing,often funny with shocking sidebars and on occasion challenging to figure out what's what. The famous witches are supported by a bright cast, then newcomers, now more established, I'll have to think for a spell, I keep losing track of whiuch witch is wicked and which is winsome/wholesome. Ah yes, Bullock's winsome while the redhead is abit wicked and wild.Good match, they make the movie less fantasy and more edgy than you'd expect from a comedy, but of a different sort. `
summary: WONDER WHAT IT'D BE LIKE IF THESE FIVE WITCHES GOT TOGETHER FOR A SPELL. JACK NICHOLSON'D LIKE IT FOR SURE.
